acupuncture treat-
ment. There are doc-
umented, proven
cases of brain and
dental surgery done
without anesthetic,
using only acupunc-
ture techniques to numb the patient.
There is no reason to‘ be prejudiced
against a certain philosophy or mode of
thinking just because it doesn’t jive with
ours. As long as it works, there’s no way
to tell who’s right and who’s wrong. The
only way of detecting if something is
valid is through experimentation. And
through experimentation, both ways are
valid. Once again, from knowing and
implementing both, one can transcend
the abilities of one or the other and per-
form what might be considered a med-

